DATA LICENSE (separate from the code above)

The MIT license above covers the FreeNIC *source code* (the pipeline, site, and
release tools in this repository).

The FreeNIC *data compilation* — the Parquet release and the 163-year
bank-aggregate spine listed in release-tools/release_v1.0.0/release_manifest.json,
served from https://data.freenic.org — is released under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0):
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

E-3 PROVISIONAL NOTE. The CC-BY-4.0 grant applies to FreeNIC's own compilation,
curation, derivation, and metadata. Individual upstream sources carry their own
terms — most are US Government / regulatory public-domain works (FFIEC, FDIC,
Federal Reserve, OCC, FRED, NCUA, SEC), but a few academic/derived sources
require citation and are governed by their source terms for the source data
itself. Where upstream terms and CC-BY-4.0 could appear to conflict, the
upstream terms govern that source's data only. This licensing note is
PROVISIONAL pending final per-source clearance review. See
release-tools/release_v1.0.0/LICENSE for the full data-license text.
